# Slidev Slide Creation & Editing Guide

## Quick Reference for Common Slide Patterns

Follow [slide-styling-guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/slide-creation/slide-styling-guidelines.mdc) to make sure slides do not overflow the page and look nice. 

### 1. Basic Slide
```markdown
---
layout: default
---
# Slide Title

- Bullet point 1
- Bullet point 2
- Bullet point 3
```

### 2. Two-Column Layout
```markdown
---
layout: default
---
# Two Column Layout

<div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
<div>

## Left Column
- Content for left side
- More points here

</div>
<div>

## Right Column
- Content for right side
- More points here

</div>
</div>
```

### 3. Code Example Slide
```markdown
---
layout: default
---
# Code Example

```js {2-3|5|all}
function example() {
  // These lines highlight first
  const value = computeSomething();
  
  return value; // Then this line highlights
}
```
```

### 4. Image Slide
```markdown
---
layout: center
---
# Image Example

<div class="flex justify-center">
  <img src="/path/to/image.jpg" class="h-60 rounded shadow" />
</div>

Caption text here
```

### 5. Section Divider
```markdown
---
layout: section
---
# New Section Title
```

### 6. Quote Slide
```markdown
---
layout: quote
---

"This is an important quote that stands out on its own slide."

<footer>Source Attribution</footer>
```

### 7. Diagram Slide
```markdown
---
layout: default
---
# Diagram Example

```mermaid
graph TD
  A[Start] --> B[Process]
