## Styling Tips

### Text Styling
- `<span class="text-red-500">Red text</span>`
- `<span class="font-bold">Bold text</span>`
- `<span class="opacity-50">Faded text</span>`
- `<span class="text-xs">Small text</span>` or `<span class="text-xl">Large text</span>`

### Layout Helpers
- `<div class="mt-4">Add margin top</div>`
- `<div class="p-4 border rounded">Boxed content</div>`
- `<div class="flex justify-between">Spaced content</div>`

### Adding Custom Styling
```markdown
<style>
h1 { color: #E06C75; }
h2 { color: #61AFEF; }
.custom-box { 
  border: 2px solid #98c379; 
  padding: 1rem;
  border-radius: 0.5rem;
}
</style>

<div class="custom-box">
  This content will be in a styled box
</div>
```

## Working with Slides

### Splitting Into Files
Main `slides.md`:
```markdown
---
theme: penguin
title: My Presentation
---

---
src: ./slides/01-intro.md
---

---
src: ./slides/02-content.md
---
```

Individual slide files (e.g., `slides/01-intro.md`):
```markdown
---
layout: cover
background: ./images/cover.jpg
---

# My Presentation
## Subtitle Here

Author Name
```

### Navigation Comments
Add comments to help navigate between slides:
```markdown
---
layout: default
---

# Slide Title

Content goes here

<!-- This comment helps mark the purpose of this slide for editing -->
```

## Testing & Refinement
1. Use Presenter Mode (press `P` while presenting) to:
   - See speaker notes
   - Check for overflowing content
   - Monitor timing

2. Test responsiveness by resizing the browser window

3. Check transitions between slides with different layouts and backgrounds 